reviews.text: Not too bad but doesn’t taste as good as other branches that I tried.
coffee is good, but foods are "always over cooked" no matter toast or noodle...
Come here regularly for my lunch and it’s as close as one can get to having Singaporean food in Hong Kong, not fantastic but good enough - laksa, mee siam and Nasi Lemak (not enough coconut milk!)

Absolutely disgusted to find out my son was served a bowl of noodles with hair in it. When he told the staff behind the counter he picked out the hair and looked away. Things happen but at least change it. If only I was there! Wrote to their office and didn't get a reply either. What happened to hygiene and service?
Favourite place for nasi lemak craving fix.. 👍🏻 Super tasty toast too!

reviews.text: 價錢貴得離地！食物種類雖多但某幾間味道一般至中下級數，易中伏。本身個餐已經貴（間間都50以上），加杯野飲不論凍熱仲要10蚊，有啲仲13蚊或15蚊，食個lunch洗咗成60幾蚊。坐埋邊啲位電話接收訊號奇差！差到都不知佢有冇裝天線！要坐靠出口啲位先收到，但嗰度又成日爆棚冇位，一到lunch時間一大堆附近兩間銀行後勤總部嘅職員出嚟食嘢，迫到死，總括而言就不推薦。
價錢年年加但份量年年減，很多食店的飯餐，連小孩也不夠飽。
Actually I didn't find anything tasty to eat. Maybe i was unlucky, but fried chicken and soup were not edible.
有多國美食店 價錢ok 最正是鐵板漢堡扒飯及鐵板和牛粒抄飯
